The TRANSACTIONS_LOG table is an audit table.
It is intentionally left empty in Phase V because it is populated automatically by database triggers implemented in Phase VII.
This ensures accurate, secure, and tamper-proof audit logging.‚Äù


4Ô∏è‚É£ DATA VALIDATION QUERIES
-- Check all tables
SELECT * FROM customers;
SELECT * FROM purchases;
SELECT * FROM rewards;
SELECT * FROM point_rules;

-- Join test
SELECT c.first_name, p.total_amount
FROM customers c
JOIN purchases p ON c.customer_id = p.customer_id;

-- Aggregation test
SELECT customer_id, SUM(points_earned - points_redeemed) AS total_points
FROM rewards
GROUP BY customer_id;

